						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Pallava Kampavarman, Year 17 = 886 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The record registers an endownment of 736 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold to the assembly Kāvadipākkam <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> vaṇinārāyaṇa-chaturvēdimangalam present at the hall called Chiṟṟambalam by a lady called Nambirāṭṭi (queen ?) the elder sister of one Tiruvānaṅgāmudi for the purpose feeding one guest <hi rend="italic">(viruttūṇar)</hi> daily.</p>						

						<p>(Published in <hi rend="italic">SII.</hi>, Vol. XII No. 104.)</p>						

